The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 December is 305,302 (35,187.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 December, there were 791 new confirmed cases (91.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 December, there were 603 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 31% (188 extra cases).
